McLeod’s Baheti Expects Inflation to Slow After Rate Increase

-- B y   P r a d i p t a   M u k h e r j e e
-- 
2011-03-17T09:42:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/mcleod-s-baheti-expects-inflation-to-slow-after-rate-increase.html
Kamal Baheti, director of finance
at  Mcleod Russel India Ltd. (MCLR) , world’s biggest tea grower,
comments on outlook for inflation after the  Reserve Bank  of
India today raised the repurchase rate to 6.75 percent and the
reverse repurchase rate to 5.75 percent. He spoke in an
interview on the telephone from Kolkata.  On economic growth:  “I don’t think the rate hikes will continue for very long.
With liquidity improvement, inflation will also come down in
three to four months. Overall growth will not be impacted.”  On affect on the company:  “Even if the interest rate goes up, we were not looking at
borrowing money and did not have plans to raise loans.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pradipta Mukherjee in Kolkata at 
 pmukherjee7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Arijit Ghosh at 
 aghosh@bloomberg.net  